==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Must
<hw>Must</hw> <pr>(m⟦ucr⟧st)</pr>, <pos>v. i. ⟦or⟧ auxiliary</pos>.
<ety>[OE. <ets>moste</ets>, a pret. generally meaning, could, was free
to, pres. <ets>mot</ets>, <ets>moot</ets>, AS. <ets>m⟦omac⟧ste</ets>,
pret. <ets>m⟦omac⟧t</ets>, pres.; akin to D. <ets>moetan</ets> to be
obliged, OS. <ets>m⟦omac⟧tan</ets> to be free, to be obliged, OHG.
<ets>muozan</ets>, G. <ets>m⟦uum⟧ssen</ets> to be obliged, Sw.
<ets>m⟦aring⟧ste</ets> must, Goth. <ets>gam⟦omac⟧tan</ets> to have
place, have room, to able; of unknown origin.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
be obliged; to be necessitated; -- expressing either physical or moral
necessity; <as>as, a man <ex>must</ex> eat for nourishment; we
<ex>must</ex> submit to the laws.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To be morally required; to be necessary or essential
to a certain quality, character, end, or result; <as>as, he
<ex>must</ex> reconsider the matter; he <ex>must</ex> have been
insane.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Likewise <qex>must</qex> the deacons be grave.</q> <rj><qau>1 Tim.
iii. 8.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Morover, he [a bishop] <qex>must</qex> have a good report of them
which are without.</q> <rj><qau>1 Tim. iii. 7.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The principal verb, if easily supplied by the mind, was
formerly often omitted when <xex>must</xex> was used; <as>as, I
<ex>must</ex> away</as>. ⟦ldquo⟧I <xex>must</xex> to Coventry.⟦rdquo⟧
<au>Shak.</au></note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Must</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Must
<hw>Must</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>must</ets>, fr. L.
<ets>mustum</ets> (sc. <ets>vinum</ets>), from <ets>mustus</ets> young,
new, fresh. Cf. <er>Mustard</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The expressed
juice of the grape, or other fruit, before fermentation.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧These men ben full of <xex>must</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Wyclif
(Acts ii. 13.).</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>No fermenting <qex>must</qex> fills . . . the deep vats.</q>
<rj><qau>Longfellow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <ety>[Cf. <er>Musty</er>.]</ety>
<def>Mustiness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Must</ent>⟦br⟧

